'''Kawasu Matsuri''' (川裾祭) is a festival held at river confluences and near river mouths. It is also known as '''Kawasu-san''' or '''Kawasso-san'''. Additionally, "Kawasu" can be written as '''川すそ''' or '''川下'''.

== Overview ==
Kawasu Matsuri is observed in various regions from {{ill|Fukui Prefecture|ja|福井県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukui Prefecture|qq=}} to the northern part of {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}}, with some festivals having religious significance. Generally, these festivals take place at river confluences or near river mouths, but some are also held along coastlines distant from river mouths.

== Major Kawasu Festivals ==
; {{ill|Takashima, Shiga|ja|高島市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashima, Shiga|qq=}}, {{ill|Makino, Shiga|ja|マキノ町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Makino, Shiga|qq=}}
: The Kawasu Matsuri here is the annual festival of {{ill|Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|ja|唐﨑神社 (高島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|qq=}}, located near {{ill|Lake Biwa|ja|琵琶湖|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lake Biwa|qq=}}. It is held on the fourth Sunday of July and is the only major summer festival in the Kosai region.

; {{ill|Takashima, Shiga|ja|高島市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashima, Shiga|qq=}}, {{ill|Shin'asu, Shiga|ja|新旭町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shin'asu, Shiga|qq=}}
: The Kawasu Matsuri (also known as "Yamagata no Kawasu-san") is the summer festival of the subsidiary {{ill|Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|ja|唐﨑神社 (高島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|qq=}} of {{ill|Nishinomiya Ōjinja|ja|西宮大神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishinomiya Ōjinja|qq=}} near Lake Biwa. Once held on July 28, it is now observed on the last Sunday of July, featuring traditional dances for entertainment until late at night.

