==Merged second translation== [[File:Asamogawa Minazuki Matsuri(2).jpg|thumb|300px|浅茂川水無月祭(京都府京丹後市網野町）]] [[File:20140729 Ichijima-Kawasuso Matsuri 市島川裾祭（丹波市市島町）竹田川DSCF0503.JPG|thumb|市島川裾祭（丹波市市島町）]]
'''Kawasuso Matsuri''' (川裾祭) is a festival held at the confluence or near the mouth of a river.<ref name="kokugo">{{Cite book|year=1983|title=日本国語大辞典|publisher={{ill|Shogakukan|ja|小学館|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogakukan|qq=}}}}</ref> It is also known as '''Kawasuso-san''' or '''Kawasso-san'''<ref name="3tan">{{Cite web|和書|title=三たん事典「人と祭り編」:川裾祭り 夏の夕べの風物詩|url=http://www.3tan.jp/1kan/kurasi/12.html|publisher=三たん地方開発促進協議会|accessdate=2012-02-03}}</ref>. Moreover, the name '''Kawasuso''' is alternatively written as '''Kawasuso''' or '''Kawashimo'''<ref name="hyogo">{{Cite book|year=1983|title=兵庫県大百科事典(上巻)|publisher={{ill|Kobe Shimbun|ja|神戸新聞社|lt=Kobe Shimbun Publishing Center|lt_ja=神戸新聞出版センター|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kobe Shimbun|qq=}}|isbn=4875211007}}</ref>.
== Overview == {{ill|Fukui Prefecture|ja|福井県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukui Prefecture|qq=}} to {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}} in the north, various locales feature this festival – sometimes as a Shinto ritual.<ref name="kokugo"/><ref name="3tan"/> Generally, it is held at a river’s confluence or near its mouth, though there are cases where it takes place along coastal areas distant from the river mouth.<ref name="hyogo"/>
== Main Kawasuso Festivals ==
; {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|ja|滋賀県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiga Prefecture|qq=}} {{ill|Takashima City|ja|高島市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashima City|qq=}} {{ill|Makino Town|ja|マキノ町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Makino Town|qq=}} : The Kawasuso Matsuri here is the annual festival of {{ill|Karasaki Shrine|ja|唐﨑神社 (高島市)|lt=Karasaki Shrine|lt_ja=唐﨑神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karasaki Shrine|qq=}}, celebrated near {{ill|Lake Biwa|ja|琵琶湖|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lake Biwa|qq=}}. It is held on the fourth Sunday of July and is the only major summer festival in the western lake region.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=神社紹介:唐崎神社|url=http://www.shiga-jinjacho.jp/ycBBS/Board.cgi/02_jinja_db/db/ycDB_02jinja-pc-detail.html?mode:view=1&view:oid=1320|publisher={{ill|Shiga Prefecture Shrine Office|ja|滋賀県神社庁|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiga Prefecture Shrine Office|qq=}}|accessdate=2012-02-03}}</ref> ; {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|ja|滋賀県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiga Prefecture|qq=}} {{ill|Takashima City|ja|高島市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashima City|qq=}} {{ill|Shin-Asahi Town|ja|新旭町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shin-Asahi Town|qq=}} : Kawasuso Matsuri (Yamagata Kawasso-san) is the summer festival of the auxiliary Karasaki Shrine of {{ill|Nishinomiya Ōjin Shrine|ja|西宮大神社 (高島市)|lt=Nishinomiya Ōjin Shrine|lt_ja=西宮大神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishinomiya Ōjin Shrine|qq=}}, located near {{ill|Lake Biwa|ja|琵琶湖|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lake Biwa|qq=}}. It was once held on July 28 but now takes place on the last Sunday of July. Following the morning ceremonies, cooling dances are performed into the late evening as part of a lively ritual. ; {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}} {{ill|Tamba City|ja|丹波市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamba City|qq=}} {{ill|Ichijima Town|ja|市島町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichijima Town|qq=}} Ichijima : {{ill|Ichijima Kawasuso Matsuri|ja|市島川裾まつり|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichijima Kawasuso Matsuri|qq=}} is a river festival of the Takeda River—a tributary of the {{ill|Yura River|ja|由良川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yura River|qq=}}—held on July 29. The event features a floating lantern ceremony and a fireworks display of approximately 750 shots.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=市島川裾祭り|url=http://www.tambacity-kankou.jp/modules/weblinks/singlelink.php?lid=63|publisher=丹波市観光協会|accessdate=2012-02-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=市島川裾祭り花火協力金募る|url=http://tanba.jp/modules/topics/index.php?page=article&storyid=4309|publisher=丹波新聞|date=2011-07-07|accessdate=2012-02-03|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504111711/http://tanba.jp/modules/topics/index.php?page=article&storyid=4309|archivedate=2016-05-04}}</ref> In Tamba City, there are also other related celebrations, such as the Original Kawasuso Matsuri ({{ill|Hikami Town|ja|氷上町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikami Town|qq=}} Hongo)<ref name="3tan"/>, Kitagoyu Kawasuso Matsuri ({{ill|Hikami Town|ja|氷上町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikami Town|qq=}} Miyu), and Narimatsu Kawasuso Matsuri ({{ill|Hikami Town|ja|氷上町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikami Town|qq=}} Narimatsu).<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=北御油川裾祭|url=http://tanba.jp/modules/piCal/index.php?action=View&event_id=0000002342|publisher=丹波新聞|accessdate=2012-02-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=成松川裾まつり|url=http://kitakinki.gr.jp/modules/piCal/index.php?smode=Monthly&action=View&event_id=0000000043&caldate=2010-7-5|publisher=北近畿広域観光連盟|accessdate=2012-02-03}}</ref> ; {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}} {{ill|Mikata District|ja|美方郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikata District|qq=}} {{ill|Shinonsen Town|ja|新温泉町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinonsen Town|qq=}} : The Kawashimo Grand Festival is a river celebration held on the Kishida, Kuto, and Tai Rivers.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=浜坂の海岸と川下大祭|url=http://www.pref.hyogo.jp/JPN/apr/hyogoshizen/reddata2011/4-13/sk191.pdf|format=pdf|publisher={{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}}|accessdate=2012-02-03}}</ref> It is the annual festival of {{ill|Utuno Shrine|ja|宇都野神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utuno Shrine|qq=}}, featuring the offering of the Kirin Lion Dance—a performance designated as an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property by Hyōgo Prefecture—and a procession in which mikoshi and other sacred objects parade through the town.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=但馬三大祭の一つ「川下大祭」 |url=http://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/f5705d2964953b4cc6a5bc751697a3b9.html|publisher={{ill|Shinonsen Town|ja|新温泉町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinonsen Town|qq=}}|accessdate=2012-02-03}}</ref> A fireworks display featuring roughly 3000 shots is also held, making it one of the {{ill|Tajima Three Great Festivals|ja|但馬三大祭り|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tajima Three Great Festivals|qq=}}. ; {{ill|Kyoto Prefecture|ja|京都府|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyoto Prefecture|qq=}} {{ill|Kyotango City|ja|京丹後市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyotango City|qq=}} {{ill|Amino Town|ja|網野町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amino Town|qq=}} : The Asamogawa Minazuki Festival (commonly known as Kawasso-san) is an annual summer celebration held on July 30 in the Asamogawa district of Amino Town, Kyotango City, Kyoto Prefecture. It features a maritime procession—known as kaijōtogyo—and an evening cooling fireworks display.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.city.kyotango.lg.jp/material/files/group/13/a_asamogawah2608_3.pdf|title=a_asamogawah2608_3.pdf|format=PDF|publisher=京丹後市|date=2013-08-19|accessdate=2022-07-30}}</ref> == See Also == * {{ill|Northern Kinki|ja|北近畿|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Northern Kinki|qq=}} * {{ill|Ichijima Kawasuso Matsuri|ja|市島川裾まつり|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichijima Kawasuso Matsuri|qq=}}
