'''Kawasu Matsuri''' (川裾祭) is a festival held at river confluences and near river mouths. It is also known as '''Kawasu-san''' or '''Kawasso-san'''. Additionally, "Kawasu" can be written as '''川すそ''' or '''川下'''.
== Overview == Kawasu Matsuri is observed in various regions from {{ill|Fukui Prefecture|ja|福井県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukui Prefecture|qq=}} to the northern part of {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}}, with some festivals having religious significance. Generally, these festivals take place at river confluences or near river mouths, but some are also held along coastlines distant from river mouths.
== Major Kawasu Festivals == ; {{ill|Takashima, Shiga|ja|高島市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashima, Shiga|qq=}}, {{ill|Makino, Shiga|ja|マキノ町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Makino, Shiga|qq=}} : The Kawasu Matsuri here is the annual festival of {{ill|Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|ja|唐﨑神社 (高島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|qq=}}, located near {{ill|Lake Biwa|ja|琵琶湖|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lake Biwa|qq=}}. It is held on the fourth Sunday of July and is the only major summer festival in the Kosai region.
; {{ill|Takashima, Shiga|ja|高島市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashima, Shiga|qq=}}, {{ill|Shin'asu, Shiga|ja|新旭町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shin'asu, Shiga|qq=}} : The Kawasu Matsuri (also known as "Yamagata no Kawasu-san") is the summer festival of the subsidiary {{ill|Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|ja|唐﨑神社 (高島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|qq=}} of {{ill|Nishinomiya Ōjinja|ja|西宮大神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishinomiya Ōjinja|qq=}} near Lake Biwa. Once held on July 28, it is now observed on the last Sunday of July, featuring traditional dances for entertainment until late at night.
; {{ill|Ichijima, Tanba|ja|市島町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichijima, Tanba|qq=}}, {{ill|Tanba, Hyōgo|ja|丹波市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanba, Hyōgo|qq=}} : The {{ill|Ichijima Kawasu Matsuri|ja|市島川裾まつり|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichijima Kawasu Matsuri|qq=}} is a river festival held along the {{ill|Takeda River (Hyōgo and Kyoto)|ja|竹田川 (兵庫県・京都府)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeda River (Hyōgo and Kyoto)|qq=}}, a tributary of the {{ill|Yura River (Japan)|ja|由良川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yura River (Japan)|qq=}}. Taking place on July 29, it features floating lanterns and a fireworks display of around 750 shells. Other related festivals in Tanba City include the "Ganso Kawasu Matsuri" in {{ill|Hikami, Hyōgo|ja|氷上町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikami, Hyōgo|qq=}}, "Kita Goi Kawasu Matsuri," and "Naramatsu Kawasu Matsuri."
; {{ill|Shin'onsen, Hyōgo|ja|新温泉町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shin'onsen, Hyōgo|qq=}}, {{ill|Mikata District, Hyōgo|ja|美方郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikata District, Hyōgo|qq=}} : The Kawashimo Grand Festival is a river festival held at the {{ill|Kishida River|ja|岸田川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishida River|qq=}}, {{ill|Kuto River|ja|久斗川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuto River|qq=}}, and {{ill|Tai River|ja|田井川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tai River|qq=}}. As the annual festival of {{ill|Utono Shrine|ja|宇都野神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utono Shrine|qq=}}, it includes performances of the {{ill|Kirin Shishi-mai|ja|麒麟獅子舞|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kirin Shishi-mai|qq=}}, designated as an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property of Hyōgo Prefecture. The festival features a procession of mikoshi (portable shrines) and a large fireworks display with around 3,000 shells, recognized as one of the {{ill|Three Great Festivals of Tajima|ja|但馬三大祭り|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Three Great Festivals of Tajima|qq=}}.
; {{ill|Amino, Kyōtango|ja|網野町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amino, Kyōtango|qq=}}, {{ill|Kyōtango, Kyoto|ja|京丹後市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōtango, Kyoto|qq=}} : The {{ill|Asamogawa Minazuki Matsuri|ja|浅茂川水無月祭|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asamogawa Minazuki Matsuri|qq=}} (commonly known as "Kawasso-san") is held annually on July 30 in Asamogawa, Amino, Kyōtango. The festival includes a sea-going mikoshi procession and concludes with a large summer fireworks display.
