{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11479133]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 07:28, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11479133]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 04:07, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Kawasu Matsuri''' (川裾祭) is a festival held at river confluences and near river mouths. It is also known as '''Kawasu-san''' or '''Kawasso-san'''. Additionally, "Kawasu" can be written as '''川すそ''' or '''川下'''.
== Overview == Kawasu Matsuri is observed in various regions from [[:en:Fukui Prefecture|Fukui Prefecture]] to the northern part of [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]], with some festivals having religious significance. Generally, these festivals take place at river confluences or near river mouths, but some are also held along coastlines distant from river mouths.
== Major Kawasu Festivals == ; [[:en:Takashima, Shiga|Takashima, Shiga]], [[:en:Makino, Shiga|Makino, Shiga]] : The Kawasu Matsuri here is the annual festival of {{ill|Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|ja|唐﨑神社 (高島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, located near [[:en:Lake Biwa|Lake Biwa]]. It is held on the fourth Sunday of July and is the only major summer festival in the Kosai region.
; [[:en:Takashima, Shiga|Takashima, Shiga]], [[:en:Shin'asahi, Shiga|Shin'asu, Shiga]] : The Kawasu Matsuri (also known as "Yamagata no Kawasu-san") is the summer festival of the subsidiary {{ill|Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|ja|唐﨑神社 (高島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karasaki Shrine (Takashima)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} of {{ill|Nishinomiya Ōjinja|ja|西宮大神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishinomiya Ōjinja|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} near Lake Biwa. Once held on July 28, it is now observed on the last Sunday of July, featuring traditional dances for entertainment until late at night.
; [[:en:Ichijima, Hyōgo|Ichijima, Tanba]], [[:en:Tanba, Hyōgo|Tanba, Hyōgo]] : The {{ill|Ichijima Kawasu Matsuri|ja|市島川裾まつり|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichijima Kawasu Matsuri|qq=|1=Ichijima Kawasuso Matsuri|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q113636826}} is a river festival held along the {{ill|Takeda River (Hyōgo and Kyoto)|ja|竹田川 (兵庫県・京都府)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeda River (Hyōgo and Kyoto)|qq=|1=Takeda River|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11599330}}, a tributary of the [[:en:Yura River (Japan)|Yura River (Japan)]]. Taking place on July 29, it features floating lanterns and a fireworks display of around 750 shells. Other related festivals in Tanba City include the "Ganso Kawasu Matsuri" in [[:en:Hikami, Hyōgo|Hikami, Hyōgo]], "Kita Goi Kawasu Matsuri," and "Naramatsu Kawasu Matsuri."
; [[:en:Shin'onsen, Hyōgo|Shin'onsen, Hyōgo]], [[:en:Mikata District, Hyōgo|Mikata District, Hyōgo]] : The Kawashimo Grand Festival is a river festival held at the {{ill|Kishida River|ja|岸田川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishida River|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Kuto River|ja|久斗川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuto River|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and {{ill|Tai River|ja|田井川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tai River|qq=|1=taigawa|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q16282088}}. As the annual festival of {{ill|Utono Shrine|ja|宇都野神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utono Shrine|qq=|1=Utsuno- Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q109594469}}, it includes performances of the {{ill|Kirin Shishi-mai|ja|麒麟獅子舞|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kirin Shishi-mai|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 麒麟獅子|1=Qilin dance|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11677329}}, designated as an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property of Hyōgo Prefecture. The festival features a procession of mikoshi (portable shrines) and a large fireworks display with around 3,000 shells, recognized as one of the {{ill|Three Great Festivals of Tajima|ja|但馬三大祭り|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Three Great Festivals of Tajima|qq=|1=Tajima Three Great Festivals|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11381623}}.
; {{ill|Amino, Kyōtango|ja|網野町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amino, Kyōtango|qq=|1=Amino|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11607240}}, [[:en:Kyōtango|Kyōtango, Kyoto]] : The {{ill|Asamogawa Minazuki Matsuri|ja|浅茂川水無月祭|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asamogawa Minazuki Matsuri|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (commonly known as "Kawasso-san") is held annually on July 30 in Asamogawa, Amino, Kyōtango. The festival includes a sea-going mikoshi procession and concludes with a large summer fireworks display.
